text:
1 Cult News Did The Walking Dead just kill off a major character? Twitter users weigh in on the latest episode Monday, Oct 26 2015, 04:03   Twitter Share on Google+ The Walking Dead returned to our screens with a record-breaking deluge of zombies earlier this month and the twists and turns have not stopped since.Sunday night's (October 25) episode in the US was no exception - only this time fans were left panicking, as it looks like one key character has come to an untimely end. With such heartbreaking news, social media had a lot to say, so Digital Spy took to Twitter to find out your thoughts on AMC's latest offering, which will contain spoilers . You have been warned. 
Â© AMC / Gene Page NSFW - The 13 most brutal deaths from 5 seasons of The Walking Dead Say it ain't so! Six seasons into the show, it looks like long-time character Glenn Rhee, played by Steven Yeun, has met his fate at the hands of an army of Walkers, and fans don't know how to cope with the news. There are those who are in denial: Please let this not be true. Please let this not be true. Please let this not be true.
